Evaluate the prefiltration processes (e.g., coagulation, flocculation and sedimentation). Coagulation is a process that uses coagulant chemicals and mixing, by which colloidal and suspended materials are destabilized and aggregated into flocs. Flocculation is the process that enhances agglutination of smaller floc particles into larger ones by stirring. Sedimentation is the process by which solids are removed by gravity separation before filtration. Observe whether these processes reduce turbidity. Calculate detention (transit) time within the settling tank and seek information about frequency and method of cleaning the tank. For example, if an 8-ft-deep sedimentation basin has a volume of 1 million gal, and the plant flow rate is 20 million gal/day, detention time in the basin is: (in your country you may want to calculate rates based on metric measurements)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
